<br>
If they're honest with themselves, they'll admit that they take damage too good at this time. It remains to be seen whether or not the nerf will swing their defense too far the other way.<br>
<br>
As it stands right now, a monk can tank nearly anywhere that a plate wearing class can in the experience gathering zones. Why would anyone take the random knight LFG when they can get a monk that will tank just as well, and do 60% more damage?<br>
<br>
The question now is, how well SHOULD they tank? <br>
<br>
My personal opinion is that they ought to tank somewhere between a ranger and rogue, able to stand up to low blue mobs quite well, but hurt bad by the tougher stuff.<br>
<br>
There was a cute little parse thread where a sk was compared to 2 monks, all tanking a krup knight in seb for one hour. The monks and SK all tanked it nearly equally. That should have been no contest.<br>
<br>
